l antioxidant that fights free radicals","Mushrooms are a natural source of Vitamin D, essential for bone health","Fenugreek seeds help regulate blood sugar levels","Mustard oil improves blood circulation and has anti-bacterial properties","Turmeric (curcumin) is a potent anti-inflammatory agent"],dosage:"1–2 tablespoons daily with meals. Best consumed with roti, paratha, or rice. Suitable for all ages above 5 years.",storage:"Store in a cool, dry place. Refrigerate after opening. Best consumed within 6 months.",weight:"250g"},{slug:"mushroom-murabba",name:"Mushroom Murabba",category:"Preserves",price:"₹349",image:Ej,tag:"New",benefit:"Supports heart health & vitamin D source",description:"A unique sweet preserve made from tender mushrooms slow-cooked in raw sugar syrup infused with saffron, cardamom, and rose water. This Ayurvedic delicacy is both a treat for your taste buds and a tonic for your heart.",ingredients:["Fresh Mushrooms","Organic Jaggery (Gud)","Saffron (Kesar)","Green Cardamom (Elaichi)","Rose Water (Gulab Jal)","Fennel Seeds (Saunf)","Black Pepper (Kali Mirch)","Honey (Shahad)"],nutrition:[{label:"Calories",value:"85 kcal per serving (30g)"},{label:"Protein",value:"1.5g"},{label:"Fat",value:"0.5g"},{label:"Carbohydrates",value:"18g"},{label:"Iron",value:"8% DV"},{label:"Vitamin D",value:"12% DV"},{label:"Potassium",value:"6% DV"}],ayurvedicBenefits:["Saffron (Kesar) improves mood, memory and acts as an anti-depressant","Mushrooms support cardiovascular health by lowering bad cholesterol","Cardamom aids digestion and freshens breath naturally","Jaggery is rich in iron, preventing anaemia","Rose water has cooling properties — balances Pitta dosha","Black pepper enhances nutrient absorption (bioavailability booster)"],dosage:"1–2 teaspoons daily, preferably in the morning on an empty stomach. Can be taken with warm milk for enhanced benefits.",storage:"Store in a glass jar in a cool, dry place. Refrigerate after opening. Shelf life: 8 months.",weight:"3